    • Method Detail

      • calcAccuracy

        public void calcAccuracy()
        It is the method that finally calculates accuracy after instantiating a RuleAccuracy object. Compare the fields in a column of a file with their fields in the Excel column It then gives us the result of accuracy (number of times IsLongMethod is equal in both files (excel file , file chosen by the user as argument in the RuleAccuracy constructor). The result of accuracy is stored in the accuracyNewRule variable, an attribute of the Rule Accuracy class.
